				<div class="et_pb_with_border et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_20 et_animated  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><h2 style="text-align: center;">Latest Posts</h2></div>
			</div><div class="et_pb_module et_pb_blog_extras et_pb_blog_extras_1">
				
				
				
				
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module_inner">
					<div class="et_pb_posts et_pb_bg_layout_light" data-scroll-top-animation="ajax_load_more,numbered_pagination,filterable_categories">
                <div class="el-dbe-blog-extra vertical_grid  el-dbe-blog-extra-slider solid_dot"><div class="swiper-container"><div class="swiper-wrapper"><article id="post-7875" class="et_pb_post et_pb_post_extra et_pb_text_align_left et-waypoint et_pb_animation_off el_dbe_vertical_grid post-7875 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-past-webinars content-type-news target-group-academics target-group-collective-members target-group-members target-group-ngos target-group-young-future-lawyers swiper-slide" ><div class="post-media"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/webinars/past-webinars/join-us-friday-3-july-2026-for-the-upcoming-extradition-challenges-webinar/" target="_self" class="entry-featured-image-url"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="512" src="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ecba-wg-webinar-annoucement-extradition-wg-3-july-2026-1600cet-NK202606261615-gs-1024x512.jpg" class="et_pb_post_main_image no-lazyload skip-lazy wp-post-image" alt="" loading="lazy" srcset="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ecba-wg-webinar-annoucement-extradition-wg-3-july-2026-1600cet-NK202606261615-gs-1024x512.jpg 1024w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ecba-wg-webinar-annoucement-extradition-wg-3-july-2026-1600cet-NK202606261615-gs-980x490.jpg 980w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ecba-wg-webinar-annoucement-extradition-wg-3-july-2026-1600cet-NK202606261615-gs-480x240.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></a></div> <!-- post-media --><div class="post-content"><h4 class="entry-title"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/webinars/past-webinars/join-us-friday-3-july-2026-for-the-upcoming-extradition-challenges-webinar/" target="_self">Join us Friday 3 July, 2026 for the upcoming Extradition Challenges webinar</a></h4><div class="post-data"><p>Heiko Ahlbrecht introduces Dr. Miguel João Costa on the CJEU&#8217;s 20 Mar 2025 judgment (C‑763/22) and its impact on conflicting extradition requests.</p>
</div></div> <!-- post-content --></article> <!-- et_pb_post_extra --><article id="post-7870" class="et_pb_post et_pb_post_extra et_pb_text_align_left et-waypoint et_pb_animation_off el_dbe_vertical_grid post-7870 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-conferences category-upcoming-conferences-and-webinars content-type-conferences target-group-academics target-group-collective-members target-group-courts target-group-members target-group-ngos target-group-policy-making-bodies target-group-young-future-lawyers swiper-slide" ><div class="post-media"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/conferences/upcoming-conferences-and-webinars/efcl-annual-conference-2027-11-june-2027-in-frankfurt-germany/" target="_self" class="entry-featured-image-url"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="512" src="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/efcl-annual-conference-2027-frankfurt-germany-2606231023-1024x512.jpg" class="et_pb_post_main_image no-lazyload skip-lazy wp-post-image" alt="" loading="lazy" srcset="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/efcl-annual-conference-2027-frankfurt-germany-2606231023-1024x512.jpg 1024w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/efcl-annual-conference-2027-frankfurt-germany-2606231023-980x490.jpg 980w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/efcl-annual-conference-2027-frankfurt-germany-2606231023-480x240.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></a></div> <!-- post-media --><div class="post-content"><h4 class="entry-title"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/conferences/upcoming-conferences-and-webinars/efcl-annual-conference-2027-11-june-2027-in-frankfurt-germany/" target="_self">EFCL Annual Conference 2027, 11 June 2027 in Frankfurt, Germany</a></h4><div class="post-data"><p>The next EFCL Conference is scheduled for 11 June 2027 in Frankfurt, Germany. Details will be published closer to the date.</p>
</div></div> <!-- post-content --></article> <!-- et_pb_post_extra --><article id="post-7858" class="et_pb_post et_pb_post_extra et_pb_text_align_left et-waypoint et_pb_animation_off el_dbe_vertical_grid post-7858 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-death-penalty-opposition category-fair-trial-standards category-human-rights-committee content-type-human-rights-statements content-type-news jurisdiction-israel target-group-academics target-group-collective-members target-group-members target-group-ngos target-group-young-future-lawyers swiper-slide" ><div class="post-media"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/human-rights-committee/ecba-issues-statement-on-the-death-penalty-legislation-in-israel/" target="_self" class="entry-featured-image-url"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="512" src="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ecba-wgs-hrc-writing-statement-2606111855-1024x512.jpg" class="et_pb_post_main_image no-lazyload skip-lazy wp-post-image" alt="" loading="lazy" srcset="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ecba-wgs-hrc-writing-statement-2606111855-1024x512.jpg 1024w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ecba-wgs-hrc-writing-statement-2606111855-980x490.jpg 980w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ecba-wgs-hrc-writing-statement-2606111855-480x240.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></a></div> <!-- post-media --><div class="post-content"><h4 class="entry-title"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/human-rights-committee/ecba-issues-statement-on-the-death-penalty-legislation-in-israel/" target="_self">ECBA issues Statement on the Death Penalty Legislation in Israel</a></h4><div class="post-data"><p>ECBA condemns Israel&#8217;s new laws expanding capital punishment by hanging, targeting Palestinians and undermining fair trial guarantees.</p>
</div></div> <!-- post-content --></article> <!-- et_pb_post_extra --><article id="post-7861" class="et_pb_post et_pb_post_extra et_pb_text_align_left et-waypoint et_pb_animation_off el_dbe_vertical_grid post-7861 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-defending-the-defence category-fair-trial-standards category-human-rights-committee category-safeguarding-independent-legal-institutions content-type-human-rights-statements content-type-news jurisdiction-tunisia target-group-academics target-group-collective-members target-group-courts target-group-members target-group-ngos target-group-young-future-lawyers swiper-slide" ><div class="post-media"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/human-rights-committee/global-coalition-condemns-attacks-on-tunisian-legal-system-39-groups-urge-protection-of-bar/" target="_self" class="entry-featured-image-url"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="512" src="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ecba-wgs-hrc-writing-statement-2606111857-1024x512.jpg" class="et_pb_post_main_image no-lazyload skip-lazy wp-post-image" alt="" loading="lazy" srcset="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ecba-wgs-hrc-writing-statement-2606111857-1024x512.jpg 1024w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ecba-wgs-hrc-writing-statement-2606111857-980x490.jpg 980w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/ecba-wgs-hrc-writing-statement-2606111857-480x240.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></a></div> <!-- post-media --><div class="post-content"><h4 class="entry-title"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/human-rights-committee/global-coalition-condemns-attacks-on-tunisian-legal-system-39-groups-urge-protection-of-bar/" target="_self">Global Coalition Condemns Attacks on Tunisian Legal System: 39 Groups Urge Protection of Bar</a></h4><div class="post-data"><p>Over thirty-nine international organisations have united to condemn Tunisia&#8217;s systemic, state-led assault on judicial independence and the rights of defense advocates.</p>
</div></div> <!-- post-content --></article> <!-- et_pb_post_extra --><article id="post-7803" class="et_pb_post et_pb_post_extra et_pb_text_align_left et-waypoint et_pb_animation_off el_dbe_vertical_grid post-7803 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-past-webinars content-type-news target-group-academics target-group-collective-members target-group-members target-group-ngos target-group-young-future-lawyers swiper-slide" ><div class="post-media"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/webinars/past-webinars/join-us-friday-22-may-2026-for-the-upcoming-sanctions-wg-webinar/" target="_self" class="entry-featured-image-url"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="512" src="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-wg-webinar-annoucement-sanctions-wg-22-may-2026-1630cet-NK202605132124-1024x512.jpg" class="et_pb_post_main_image no-lazyload skip-lazy wp-post-image" alt="" loading="lazy" srcset="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-wg-webinar-annoucement-sanctions-wg-22-may-2026-1630cet-NK202605132124-1024x512.jpg 1024w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-wg-webinar-annoucement-sanctions-wg-22-may-2026-1630cet-NK202605132124-980x490.jpg 980w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-wg-webinar-annoucement-sanctions-wg-22-may-2026-1630cet-NK202605132124-480x240.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></a></div> <!-- post-media --><div class="post-content"><h4 class="entry-title"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/webinars/past-webinars/join-us-friday-22-may-2026-for-the-upcoming-sanctions-wg-webinar/" target="_self">Join us Friday 22 May, 2026 for the upcoming Sanctions WG webinar</a></h4><div class="post-data"><p>Elena Fedorova and Anzhela Torosyan will discuss the Advocate General&#8217;s Opinion in the DNO Yémen AS case before the CJEU, issued on 19 March 2026 (C-842/24), and its practical consequences for arbitration proceedings.</p>
</div></div> <!-- post-content --></article> <!-- et_pb_post_extra --><article id="post-7331" class="et_pb_post et_pb_post_extra et_pb_text_align_left et-waypoint et_pb_animation_off el_dbe_vertical_grid post-7331 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-past-webinars content-type-news target-group-academics target-group-collective-members target-group-members target-group-ngos target-group-young-future-lawyers swiper-slide" ><div class="post-media"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/webinars/past-webinars/join-us-friday-15-may-2026-for-the-upcoming-extradition-challenges-webinar/" target="_self" class="entry-featured-image-url"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="512" src="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-wg-webinar-annoucement-extradition-wg-15-may-2026-1600cet-NK202605131311-1024x512.jpg" class="et_pb_post_main_image no-lazyload skip-lazy wp-post-image" alt="Join us Friday 15 May, 2026 for the upcoming Extradition Challenges webinar" loading="lazy" srcset="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-wg-webinar-annoucement-extradition-wg-15-may-2026-1600cet-NK202605131311-1024x512.jpg 1024w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-wg-webinar-annoucement-extradition-wg-15-may-2026-1600cet-NK202605131311-980x490.jpg 980w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-wg-webinar-annoucement-extradition-wg-15-may-2026-1600cet-NK202605131311-480x240.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></a></div> <!-- post-media --><div class="post-content"><h4 class="entry-title"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/webinars/past-webinars/join-us-friday-15-may-2026-for-the-upcoming-extradition-challenges-webinar/" target="_self">Join us Friday 15 May, 2026 for the upcoming Extradition Challenges webinar</a></h4><div class="post-data"><p>A Brussels court ordered Belgium to negotiate the return of a wrongly extradited person to the US — a landmark case discussed with Belgian defence lawyer Christophe Marchand.</p>
</div></div> <!-- post-content --></article> <!-- et_pb_post_extra --><article id="post-1635" class="et_pb_post et_pb_post_extra et_pb_text_align_left et-waypoint et_pb_animation_off el_dbe_vertical_grid post-1635 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-past-conferences content-type-conferences target-group-academics target-group-collective-members target-group-courts target-group-members target-group-ngos target-group-policy-making-bodies target-group-young-future-lawyers swiper-slide" ><div class="post-media"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/conferences/past-conferences/efcl-annual-conference-2026-12-june-2026-in-london-united-kingdom/" target="_self" class="entry-featured-image-url"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="512" src="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ecba-conferences-efcl-annual-conference-london-2026-202601191230-1024x512.jpg" class="et_pb_post_main_image no-lazyload skip-lazy wp-post-image" alt="" loading="lazy" srcset="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ecba-conferences-efcl-annual-conference-london-2026-202601191230-1024x512.jpg 1024w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ecba-conferences-efcl-annual-conference-london-2026-202601191230-980x490.jpg 980w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/ecba-conferences-efcl-annual-conference-london-2026-202601191230-480x240.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></a></div> <!-- post-media --><div class="post-content"><h4 class="entry-title"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/conferences/past-conferences/efcl-annual-conference-2026-12-june-2026-in-london-united-kingdom/" target="_self">EFCL Annual Conference 2026, 12 June 2026 in London, United Kingdom</a></h4><div class="post-data"><p>Join the next EFCL Conference which will be a joint conference with the FLA in London!</p>
</div></div> <!-- post-content --></article> <!-- et_pb_post_extra --><article id="post-7797" class="et_pb_post et_pb_post_extra et_pb_text_align_left et-waypoint et_pb_animation_off el_dbe_vertical_grid post-7797 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-fair-trial-standards category-human-rights-committee category-safeguarding-independent-legal-institutions content-type-news target-group-academics target-group-collective-members target-group-courts target-group-members target-group-ngos target-group-policy-making-bodies target-group-young-future-lawyers swiper-slide" ><div class="post-media"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/human-rights-committee/the-ecba-cautions-against-rebalancing-fundamental-rights-at-upcoming-coe-session/" target="_self" class="entry-featured-image-url"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="512" src="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-hrc-strassbourg-202605132008-1024x512.jpg" class="et_pb_post_main_image no-lazyload skip-lazy wp-post-image" alt="" loading="lazy" srcset="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-hrc-strassbourg-202605132008-1024x512.jpg 1024w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-hrc-strassbourg-202605132008-980x490.jpg 980w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-hrc-strassbourg-202605132008-480x240.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></a></div> <!-- post-media --><div class="post-content"><h4 class="entry-title"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/human-rights-committee/the-ecba-cautions-against-rebalancing-fundamental-rights-at-upcoming-coe-session/" target="_self">The ECBA Cautions Against &#8220;Rebalancing&#8221; Fundamental Rights at Upcoming CoE Session</a></h4><div class="post-data"><p>Ahead of the May 2026 Chişinău Ministerial Session, the ECBA warns that proposed migration-driven &#8220;rebalancing&#8221; of ECHR rights risks weakening the rule of law. Read our observations.</p>
</div></div> <!-- post-content --></article> <!-- et_pb_post_extra --><article id="post-7820" class="et_pb_post et_pb_post_extra et_pb_text_align_left et-waypoint et_pb_animation_off el_dbe_vertical_grid post-7820 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-fair-trial-standards category-human-rights-committee content-type-news jurisdiction-turkey target-group-academics target-group-collective-members target-group-courts target-group-members target-group-ngos target-group-policy-making-bodies target-group-young-future-lawyers swiper-slide" ><div class="post-media"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/human-rights-committee/grand-chamber-finds-violation-of-article-7-in-yasak-v-turkiye-the-ecba-welcomes-a-judgment-it-helped-shape/" target="_self" class="entry-featured-image-url"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="512" src="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/ecba-wgs-hrc-justice-scale-law-court-202605140015-1024x512.jpg" class="et_pb_post_main_image no-lazyload skip-lazy wp-post-image" alt="" loading="lazy" srcset="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/ecba-wgs-hrc-justice-scale-law-court-202605140015-1024x512.jpg 1024w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/ecba-wgs-hrc-justice-scale-law-court-202605140015-980x490.jpg 980w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/ecba-wgs-hrc-justice-scale-law-court-202605140015-480x240.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></a></div> <!-- post-media --><div class="post-content"><h4 class="entry-title"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/human-rights-committee/grand-chamber-finds-violation-of-article-7-in-yasak-v-turkiye-the-ecba-welcomes-a-judgment-it-helped-shape/" target="_self">Grand Chamber Finds Violation of Article 7 in Yasak v. Türkiye: The ECBA Welcomes a Judgment It Helped Shape</a></h4><div class="post-data"><p>The ECBA welcomes the Grand Chamber’s judgment in Yasak v. Türkiye, affirming that Article 7 prohibits retroactive punishment and requires individualized proof of criminal intent.</p>
</div></div> <!-- post-content --></article> <!-- et_pb_post_extra --><article id="post-5754" class="et_pb_post et_pb_post_extra et_pb_text_align_left et-waypoint et_pb_animation_off el_dbe_vertical_grid post-5754 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-business-crime category-cybercrime-tech-ai category-detention category-e-evidence category-evidence category-financial-crime-aml category-human-rights-committee category-human-rights-recognition category-past-conferences category-procedural-safeguards category-protest-defence-rights content-type-conferences target-group-academics target-group-collective-members target-group-courts target-group-members target-group-ngos target-group-young-future-lawyers swiper-slide" ><div class="post-media"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/human-rights-committee/ecba-spring-conference-2026-24-and-25-april-in-barcelona-spain/" target="_self" class="entry-featured-image-url"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="512" src="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-spring-conference-2026-24-and-25-april-in-barcelona-spain-group-photo-1024x512.jpg" class="et_pb_post_main_image no-lazyload skip-lazy wp-post-image" alt="ECBA Spring Conference 2026, 24 and 25 April in Barcelona, Spain" loading="lazy" srcset="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-spring-conference-2026-24-and-25-april-in-barcelona-spain-group-photo-1024x512.jpg 1024w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-spring-conference-2026-24-and-25-april-in-barcelona-spain-group-photo-980x490.jpg 980w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/ecba-spring-conference-2026-24-and-25-april-in-barcelona-spain-group-photo-480x240.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></a></div> <!-- post-media --><div class="post-content"><h4 class="entry-title"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/human-rights-committee/ecba-spring-conference-2026-24-and-25-april-in-barcelona-spain/" target="_self">ECBA Spring Conference 2026, 24 and 25 April in Barcelona, Spain</a></h4><div class="post-data"><p>The conference brought together European criminal defence lawyers for expert discussions on procedural safeguards, fundamental rights and cross-border defence practice.</p>
</div></div> <!-- post-content --></article> <!-- et_pb_post_extra --><article id="post-7056" class="et_pb_post et_pb_post_extra et_pb_text_align_left et-waypoint et_pb_animation_off el_dbe_vertical_grid post-7056 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-corruption-bribery category-current-and-future-initiatives-business-crime-wg content-type-news target-group-academics target-group-collective-members target-group-members target-group-ngos target-group-policy-making-bodies target-group-young-future-lawyers swiper-slide" ><div class="post-media"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/business-crime/corruption-bribery/writing-a-new-statement-on-the-directive-on-combatting-corruption/" target="_self" class="entry-featured-image-url"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="512" src="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/ecba-wgs-writing-laptop-table-20260421119-1024x512.jpg" class="et_pb_post_main_image no-lazyload skip-lazy wp-post-image" alt="" loading="lazy" srcset="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/ecba-wgs-writing-laptop-table-20260421119-1024x512.jpg 1024w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/ecba-wgs-writing-laptop-table-20260421119-980x490.jpg 980w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/ecba-wgs-writing-laptop-table-20260421119-480x240.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></a></div> <!-- post-media --><div class="post-content"><h4 class="entry-title"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/business-crime/corruption-bribery/writing-a-new-statement-on-the-directive-on-combatting-corruption/" target="_self">Writing a new Statement on the Directive on Combatting Corruption</a></h4><div class="post-data"><p>Preparing an ECBA follow-up position on the final EU Anti-Corruption Directive, assessing reforms and remaining defence-rights concerns in Europe’s evolving enforcement framework.</p>
</div></div> <!-- post-content --></article> <!-- et_pb_post_extra --><article id="post-7053" class="et_pb_post et_pb_post_extra et_pb_text_align_left et-waypoint et_pb_animation_off el_dbe_vertical_grid post-7053 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-current-and-future-initiatives-human-rights-committee category-fair-trial-standards content-type-news target-group-academics target-group-collective-members target-group-courts target-group-members target-group-ngos target-group-young-future-lawyers swiper-slide" ><div class="post-media"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/human-rights-committee/fair-trial-standards/strategic-litigation-and-court-interventions/" target="_self" class="entry-featured-image-url"><img decoding="async" width="1024" height="512" src="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/ecba-wgs-hrc-filing-cases-interventions-202604211135-1024x512.jpg" class="et_pb_post_main_image no-lazyload skip-lazy wp-post-image" alt="" loading="lazy" srcset="https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/ecba-wgs-hrc-filing-cases-interventions-202604211135-1024x512.jpg 1024w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/ecba-wgs-hrc-filing-cases-interventions-202604211135-980x490.jpg 980w, https://site.ecba.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/ecba-wgs-hrc-filing-cases-interventions-202604211135-480x240.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) and (max-width: 980px) 980px, (min-width: 981px) 1024px, 100vw" /></a></div> <!-- post-media --><div class="post-content"><h4 class="entry-title"><a href="https://site.ecba.org/working-groups/human-rights-committee/fair-trial-standards/strategic-litigation-and-court-interventions/" target="_self">Strategic litigation and court interventions</a></h4><div class="post-data"><p>The HRC files third-party interventions and amicus briefs in landmark cases before European and domestic courts, ensuring the criminal defence bar shapes the law that governs it.</p>
</div></div> <!-- post-content --></article> <!-- et_pb_post_extra --></div> <!-- swiper-wrapper --></div> <!-- swiper-container --><div class="swiper-pagination"></div></div> <!-- el-dbe-blog-extra -->
